&nbsp;
<div </div
It must be excluded "the cause of justification of self-defense, disposing its structural elements". To write it the gip of Rome in the 14 pages of precautionary ordinance that led to the arrest of Antonio Micarelli, the 56-year vigilante who killed, with a gunshot, Antonio Ciurciumel, the Romanian thief of 24 years, surprised to steal at the house of the neighbor in Via Cassia, in Rome.
<h2>Gip:&nbsp;no legitimate defence</h2>
"The fact that Micarelli shot not any subject, but to the criminals who had just completed a robbery is not enough to exclude the danger of reiteration - it still reads in the cards - as the man did not just shoot shots in the air to remove them, but he threw himself without scruples whatsoever in a real manhunt, which he did not stop even after the attempt to kill one after the other".
&nbsp;
"These circumstances are even more serious - the gip emphasizes - only that you consider the profession of security guard carried out by the investigator, which should well know the burdensome responsibilities on those who are authorized to carry a firearm and should not make use of it to try to remove life to someone, if not in cases where this proves absolutely necessary."
&nbsp;
" Such a reaction, evidently disproportionate and totally deprived of any self-control, denotes the lack of the most natural form of respect that should be nourished for any human life and is indicative of an indole spregiudicated and extremely dangerous - he concludes - before which it must be considered that the custody in prison is the only measure suitable to safeguard the precautionary needs". &nbsp;
Reconstruction
According to the reconstructions of the carabinieri and pm of Rome, in the evening of Thursday, February 6, Micarelli would explode gunshots when it was no longer necessary to defend itself, ie it would fire while the mischiefs were running away. The gun charger in those fringes was dumped.
At least ten bullets that would have exploded. >Fondamental for dynamic reconstruction were the images of video surveillance cameras in the area that framed Micarelli. The sworn guard commented the facts about his involvement as necessary to the defense of the neighbor and talking about the danger to his person.
"I saw the car coming against me, I didn't know what they had and if they had guns inside," said Micarelli. A reconstruction that, despite being initially supported by the testimonies of the neighbors, was refuted by video footage of the cameras, > in which you see the man chasing the thieves on the run trying before shooting at one, then to another and finally hitting in front of Antonio Ciurciumel from a very close distance, while he was trying to overrun a fence to escape. Anna, 21, wife of the victim - in an interview with Il Corriere della Sera -, said: "I'm sure he made the robbery wrong. He should have thought he was in danger. That the law must be respected. He was wrong. I scream, as strong as I can. Because I feel the world. But he didn't have to die." &nbsp;>
